    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acscentsci_3c00800__task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The ENPKG workflow follows three stages: Data acquisition (A), Data processing (B) and Data integration (C)... The raw DDA data are (1) processed using MZmine feature finding, (2a) organized in a sample-wise directory architecture... (3) taxonomical metadata standardization and uniformization using Open Tree Taxonomy matching and Wikidata cross-links, (4) molecular networks generation via matchms, (5) structural annotation using ISDB matching coupled to taxonomical and chemical consistency reweighting, and (6) structural annotation using SIRIUS and CSI:FingerID and chemical class annotation using CANOPUS. Once the processing is done, the generated data, information, and knowledge (DIK) are integrated into a single KG.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the complete ENPKG workflow from raw LC-MS2 data through feature detection, annotation, and knowledge graph integration.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "What is the complete computational workflow executed by ENPKG from raw input data to final knowledge-graph-ready annotated outputs?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:53.117637+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acscentsci_3c00800__task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The Experimental Natural Products Knowledge Graph (ENPKG) framework combines a sample-centric approach with semantic enrichment to organize large heterogeneous metabolomics data sets as a knowledge graph.",
      "asbval:note": "ENPKG is the primary framework described throughout the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ENPKG",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:53.117637+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acscentsci_3c00800__task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The resulting data are usually processed to obtain a list of LC-MS features\u2014a chromatographic peak with a given m/z, retention time (RT), area/intensity\u2014and their associated MS2 spectrum... The features from all considered samples are then classically aligned based on their RT and m/z to obtain a feature quantification table of dimensions N \u00d7 M (N represents the number of samples and M the number of features) and their associated fragmentation spectra.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes generation of feature tables with quantification and spectral data. Confidence scores are implicit in annotation outputs (e.g., COSMIC and ZODIAC scores mentioned for SIRIUS annotations).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Annotated feature table with molecular identifications and confidence scores",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:53.117637+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acscentsci_3c00800__task_002/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The previously generated set of data and information are then semantically enriched to construct a KG structure; for this, the next steps require the representation of data as subject\u2013predicate\u2013object (RDF triple)... All the above-generated data are formatted in RDF turtle format (.ttl files) using the RDFlib python package, shared in Zenodo repositories at the ENPKG Zenodo community, and gathered as a single KG managed using GraphDB.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes RDF triple generation and RDF turtle (.ttl) format output.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Knowledge-graph output files in standardized format (RDF triples or equivalent)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:53.117637+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acscentsci_3c00800__task_002/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In addition to the quantification table, different extracts' metadata, such as taxonomic position of the biosource or bioactivity, can be integrated into the FBMN to enhance its analysis and interpretation... FBMN is a technique used to organize features' fragmentation spectra in spectral similarity clusters for visualization and analysis... Molecular networking (MN) has appeared in recent years as a revolutionary solution to organize and explore large spectral data sets.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes feature-based molecular networking (FBMN) and molecular networking (MN) as visualization outputs. Spectral matching is performed via ISDB-LOTUS and SIRIUS/CSI:FingerID.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Spectral library matches and molecular network visualization outputs",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:45:53.117637+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acscentsci_3c00800__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card's research question is appropriately scoped to the ENPKG workflow as described in the paper's abstract and introduction.",
        "The expected outputs align with the paper's description of the three-stage workflow (data acquisition, processing, integration) and final KG outputs.",
        "No significant scope drift detected; the card accurately captures the end-to-end pipeline execution described in the paper."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
