      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The NPClassifier taxonomy of all 2D structures were retrieved by submitting their anisomeric SMILES to the NPClassifier API. Finally, the 2D InChiKeys were mapped against all WD compounds... all chemical structures are classified using the NPClassifier chemical taxonomy (at the pathway, superclass, and class levels).",
      "asbval:note": "Tool and role confirmed. Paper describes NPClassifier integration for chemical taxonomy classification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "NPClassifier \u2014 Provides natural product classification ontology integrated into compound metadata within the graph",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:47:43.088488+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The ENPKG workflow follows three stages: Data acquisition (A), Data processing (B) and Data integration (C)... All the scripts used for this data treatment are available for examination and reuse on the ENPKG GitHub organization, with an overview of the workflow and the links to the different repositories available at https://github.com/enpkg/enpkg_workflow.",
      "asbval:note": "ENPKG is the overarching framework described throughout the paper. The card lists it as a tool with metadata fields (version_used, install, canonical_url) that are null or empty, which is appropriate given the paper does not specify a versioned release.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ENPKG (as a tool with related_skills, version_used, etc.)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:47:43.088488+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Data processing: The raw DDA data are (1) processed using MZmine feature finding, (2a) organized in a sample-wise directory architecture... (3) taxonomical metadata standardization and uniformization using Open Tree Taxonomy matching and Wikidata cross-links, (4) molecular networks generation via matchms, (5) structural annotation using ISDB matching coupled to taxonomical and chemical consistency reweighting, and (6) structural annotation using SIRIUS and CSI:FingerID and chemical class annotation using CANOPUS. Once the processing is done, the generated data, information, and knowledge (DIK) are integrated into a single KG.",
      "asbval:note": "Scope claim is fully supported. Paper describes the sequential workflow where annotation steps precede KG integration.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill after completing all per-sample annotation steps (molecular networking, ISDB/spectral matching, SIRIUS/CSI:FingerID, and compounds metadata enhancement with Wikidata IDs and NPClassifier ontology).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:47:43.088488+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A KG can store complex and heterogeneous data, which can be organized and interpreted using the graph topology... These graphs can be queried using the SPARQL Protocol and RDF Query Language (SPARQL)... Because the RDF is a W3C standard, KGs are interoperable, and it is possible to elaborate federated queries over multiple end points to retrieve and link data from different RDF databases (DBs).",
      "asbval:note": "Scope claim is fully supported. Paper emphasizes heterogeneous data integration, SPARQL querying, and federated query capability.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use when the goal is to integrate heterogeneous metabolomics outputs into a unified, SPARQL-queryable knowledge graph that can be merged with other samples or external knowledge bases.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:47:43.088488+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Once the processing is done, the generated data, information, and knowledge (DIK) are integrated into a single KG... Each sample is considered individually for taxonomic metadata standardization, feature detection, structural annotation, and FBMN. The resulting standardized data and information from all considered samples are then integrated into a single knowledge graph (KG).",
      "asbval:note": "Scope claim is supported by implication. Paper makes clear that KG integration occurs after all annotation steps are complete.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "knowledge-graph-generation-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input data are not yet fully annotated (e.g., raw spectral features lack molecular network assignment or structural prediction)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:47:43.088488+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-networking-construction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Molecular networking (MN) has appeared in recent years as a revolutionary solution to organize and explore large spectral data sets. While MN offers an efficient way to display spectral similarities... FBMN is a technique used to organize features' fragmentation spectra in spectral similarity clusters for visualization and analysis.",
      "asbval:note": "Research question directly supported by paper's description of MN purpose and application.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-networking-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Generate a Molecular Network (MN) from LC-MS/MS DDA fragmentation spectra to group related compounds and enable spectral similarity-based annotation and structural relationships across a metabolomics dataset.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:48:05.620762+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-networking-construction/001",
