    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/package-version-compatibility-checking/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The ENPKG workflow follows three stages: Data acquisition (A), Data processing (B) and Data integration (C)... All the scripts used for this data treatment are available on the ENPKG GitHub organization, with an overview of the workflow and the links to the different repositories available at https://github.com/enpkg/enpkg_workflow and at https://github.com/enpkg/enpkg_full.",
      "asbval:note": "ENPKG is confirmed as a computational workflow with publicly available scripts and repositories on GitHub. However, the paper does not discuss dependency checking, version compatibility verification, or environment validation as part of ENPKG setup or execution. The card's claim about 'compatibility check ensures all ENPKG submodules and dependencies are correctly installed' is not supported by the paper\u2014the paper describes ENPKG's data processing workflow, not its dependency management or validation procedures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "package-version-compatibility-checking",
