    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/python-dependency-resolution-and-pinning/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The ENPKG workflow requires LC-HRMS2 data and associated metadata as input. ... The data for each sample are processed to perform feature detection and export the resulting files (Figure 2B, step 1), here, using MZmine. ... chemical structure annotation using SIRIUS/CSI:FingerID and CANOPUS annotation. ... Interaction with the generated ENPKG is achieved through the SPARQL query module of the GraphDB instance.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that ENPKG is a multi-stage workflow that integrates MZmine, SIRIUS, and SPARQL engines, supporting the 'when to use' scenario.",
