    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/repository-cloning-and-structure-navigation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The NPClassifier taxonomy of all 2D structures were retrieved by submitting their anisomeric SMILES to the NPClassifier API. Finally, the 2D InChiKeys were mapped against all WD compounds to retrieve the corresponding WD ID... The script used for this processing is available at https://github.com/enpkg/enpkg_full/blob/d625e1a7a3365dd2fd70c66b00f8a59a80fd97a3/05_enpkg_meta_analysis/src/chemo_info_fetcher.py. [And:] To allow for faster identification of compounds with an already reported activity against a given target, we implemented an automatic fetching and formatting of ChEMBL compounds... The script used for this step is available at https://github.com/enpkg/enpkg_full/blob/d625e1a7a3365dd2fd70c66b00f8a59a80fd97a3/05_enpkg_meta_analysis/src/download_chembl.py.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly references enpkg_meta_analysis for NPClassifier retrieval, Wikidata ID mapping, and ChEMBL integration.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acscentsci-3c00800",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
